The paper deals with distributed algorithms for constructing sparse spanners and emulators in graphs, which are topics related to distributed computing (cs.DC), graph algorithms (cs.DS), network algorithms (cs.NE), computational geometry (cs.CG), and approximation algorithms (cs.AL). The abstract mentions the CONGEST and PRAM models, which are commonly used in distributed computing and parallel algorithms. Therefore, these five categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
